In [88]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 30))

for i in range(1, 21):
    estimator = KMeans(n_clusters=i)
    ids = estimator.fit_predict(processed_data[['', ' ']])

    plt.subplot(10, 2, i)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.title("K value = {}".format(i))
    plt.xlabel('')
    plt.ylabel(' ')
    plt.scatter(processed_data[''], processed_data[' '], c=ids, cmap='viridis')

    centroids = estimator.cluster_centers_
    plt.scatter(centroids[:, 0], centroids[:, 1], c='red', marker='X')

plt.show()

estimator = KMeans(n_clusters=4)
ids = estimator.fit_predict(processed_data[['', ' ']])

centroids = estimator.cluster_centers_
cluster_labels = estimator.labels_

#     
center_indices = []
for cluster_idx, centroid in enumerate(centroids):
    #      
    closest_index = np.argmin(np.linalg.norm(processed_data[['', ' ']].values - centroid, axis=1))
    #       
    center_indices.append((cluster_idx, closest_index))

#  
for cluster_idx, closest_index in center_indices:
    print("Cluster {}: Index {}".format(cluster_idx, closest_index))
